  "texts": [
    "By introducing a sophisticated error correction framework, this study seeks to establish a benchmark for error resilience in LLMs and contribute substantially to the enhancement of language-specific model reliability.",
    "This is particularly significant given the increasing reliance on LLMs for a wide range of applications in diverse linguistic and cultural landscapes.",
    "D. Major Contributions1) The development and integration of an advanced automated error correction system within the Chinese Large Language Model, Kimi, which significantly enhances the model's accuracy, precision, and recall.",
    "This improvement is reflected in key performance metrics and contributes to a more reliable user experience.2) The implementation of a dynamic feedback loop mechanism that allows for real-time adaptation of the model based on user interactions.",
    "This feedback system is designed to continuously refine the error detection and correction processes, reducing the overall error rate and enhancing system responsiveness and adaptability."
